  "float128_caveat": "numpy.float128 on x86_64 Linux is 80-bit extended precision (64-bit explicit mantissa, 15-bit exponent), NOT IEEE binary128 (113-bit mantissa, 15-bit exponent). Its subnormal range (2^(-16445)) is far below float64's smallest representable value, so the fractions.Fraction-based exact verification used in this audit cannot directly handle float128 subnormal pairs. Proper float128 testing requires either: (a) numpy.float128-aware exact arithmetic (custom bit-pattern extraction), or (b) extending the audit to use mpmath for exact rational computation across formats. Both are Phase next items. BACL's proof structure is format-agnostic \u2014 the binade-spacing argument applies to any binary float lattice \u2014 but explicit empirical verification at float128 is deferred.",
